  "prompt": "How high a percentage should one get to get the Vidyamandir FCC?",
  "response": "Vidyamandir Classes (VMC) offers Fee Concession based on performance in their entrance tests and other factors. The percentage required to get the FCC varies each year and depends on the following factors:\n\n*   **Overall performance in the entrance test:** Generally, scoring very high on the test significantly increases your chances of getting a good concession.\n*   **Number of students appearing and their relative performance:** If many students score very high, the cutoffs for FCC will be higher.\n*   **VMC's policy for that particular year:** VMC may change the criteria or the number of FCCs they offer each year.\n\nSince the cutoffs are dynamic and depend on these variables, it's hard to provide a specific percentage that guarantees an FCC.\n\n**How to Improve Your Chances:**\n\n1.  **Prepare Thoroughly:** Study the syllabus well and practice with previous years' papers.\n2.  **Aim for a High Score:** Target scoring as high as possible, exceeding 90% or even higher.\n3.  **Inquire Directly:** The best way to know the approximate range is to contact VMC directly after taking the test. They may be able to provide some insights or historical data (although they usually don't give exact figures).\n\n**In summary, aim for the highest score possible in the VMC entrance test, as a very high score greatly increases your chances of getting the Fee Concession.**",
